Week 1 : Statistic in R

Upload all required packages in R

library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(statsr)

Dataset 1: Dr. Arbuthnots Baptism Records

Upload dataset in R

To get you started, run the following command to load the data.

data(arbuthnot)

Plot number of girls baptized per year

ggplot(data = arbuthnot, aes(x = year, y = girls)) +
  geom_point()

Plot number of boys baptized per year

ggplot(data = arbuthnot, aes(x = year, y = boys)) +
  geom_point()

Plot the total VS year graph

ggplot(data = arbuthnot, aes(x = year, y = total)) +
  geom_line()

Add geom_point in the plot graph

ggplot(data = arbuthnot, aes(x = year, y = total)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point()

Plot graph for boys VS year

ggplot(data = arbuthnot, aes(x = year, y = boys)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point()

Add new column to dataset to check if boys > girls = TRUE

arbuthnot <- arbuthnot %>%
  mutate(more_boys = boys > girls)

present <- present %>%
